Key Match Events: Josh Inglis smashed a century as Scotland suffered a 70-run defeat in the second T20 international in Edinburgh.
Travis Head was dismissed for a duck in the first over.
Josh Inglis hit seven fours and seven maximums on his way to 103, with a strike rate over 200.
Brandon McMullen claimed a half-century for Scotland.
Currie dismissed Jake Fraser-McGurk with the Aussies on 23 for two.
Marcus Stoinis scored 20 not out and took four wickets for 23 runs.
George Munsey scored 19 from nine balls for Scotland.
Scotland were bowled out for 126 in reply.
